Phase 8.3 — Production Live Feed + Provider Fallback + Market-Hours Polling + Universe Import + Slack Reliability

Goal:
Make ChakraOps actually run with real-time market data in production-like local mode.
Primary provider must be ThetaTerminal v3 over HTTP (localhost:25503). Fallback to yfinance for stock-only. If both fail, run snapshot-only mode with clear UI warnings.
Add scheduled polling during market hours and reliable Slack alerts for drift + gate status changes.

Requirements:
1) Market data providers
- Implement a MarketDataProvider interface with:
  - health_check() -> (ok: bool, detail: str)
  - fetch_underlying_prices(symbols) -> dict[symbol, price]
  - fetch_option_chain_availability(symbols) -> dict[symbol, bool]
  - (optional) fetch_iv_greeks(...) if chain data supported
- Providers:
  A) ThetaTerminalHttpProvider (PRIMARY)
     - Base URL: http://127.0.0.1:25503
     - Use existing ThetaTerminal endpoints. Add a robust health check (any simple endpoint returning 200).
     - If ThetaTerminal is not reachable, return structured errors; do not crash.
  B) YFinanceProvider (FALLBACK)
     - Install/use yfinance only for underlying prices.
     - Mark option_chain_available=False and never claim Greeks/IV are available.
  C) SnapshotOnlyProvider (LAST RESORT)
     - Uses latest stored snapshot prices only.

- Update app/market/live_market_adapter.py to select provider in this order:
  ThetaTerminalHttpProvider -> YFinanceProvider -> SnapshotOnlyProvider
  Record which provider is active in LiveMarketData.data_source and include errors list.

2) Market-hours polling + UI refresh
- Add a small market-hours utility:
  - Use US/Eastern time.
  - If you can, use a market calendar lib; if not, implement a pragmatic weekday 9:30–16:00 ET check (ok for now).
- Polling cadence:
  - Market open: every 30 seconds
  - Market closed: disable polling OR poll every 5 minutes max in “snapshot-only mode”
- Ensure Streamlit autorefresh uses these intervals and clearly shows mode:
  - “LIVE (ThetaTerminal)” or “LIVE (yfinance, stocks-only)” or “SNAPSHOT ONLY (market closed / provider down)”

3) Drift detector improvements
- Keep drift read-only.
- Add configurable thresholds:
  - price_drift_warn_pct default 0.75%
  - iv_drift_abs default 0.03, iv_drift_rel default 0.15
  - spread_widened_mult default 1.5 or spread/mid > 0.20
- Severity:
  - CHAIN_UNAVAILABLE => BLOCK
  - SPREAD_WIDENED / IV_DRIFT => WARN
  - PRICE_DRIFT => INFO or WARN if above threshold
- Update Slack formatting to include severity and top items.

4) Slack alert reliability
- Ensure send_decision_alert is called on schedule during market hours (not only on manual runs).
- Only post when:
  - gate status changes OR
  - drift severity is WARN/BLOCK OR
  - once per day “heartbeat” summary (optional, behind a flag)
- Add config/env validation at startup: if Slack webhook missing, show warning in UI and log once.

5) Universe import from CSV
- Add a small import utility that reads ChakraOps_Core_Watchlist.csv (path configurable) and upserts into symbol_universe table:
  - enabled = true
  - notes = "core_watchlist"
- Add symbol normalization mapping for providers (e.g., BRK.B to BRK-B where needed), but store canonical symbol in DB.

6) UI cleanup
- Remove hardcoded “v7 step 1” strings.
- Title should be “ChakraOps – Live Decision Monitor”.
- Show active provider + last update + mode warnings prominently.

Tests:
- Unit tests for provider selection logic (Theta ok -> pick Theta; Theta down -> yfinance; all down -> snapshot-only)
- Unit tests for market-hours function and polling interval choice
- Drift threshold tests (warn vs info classification)
- CSV import upsert test (idempotent)

